HEADWORD: Aspalathus
<hw>As*pal"a*thus</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>aspalathus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A thorny shrub yielding a fragrant oil.</def> <au>Ecclus. xxiv. 15.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A genus of plants of the natural order <ord>Leguminos⟦ae⟧</ord>. The species are chiefly natives of the Cape of Good Hope.</def>⟦br⟧
